<task id="027" project="email-communication-solution-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Draft mode ‚Äî load/save draft + send-transition (statuscode Draft ‚Üí Sent)</title>
    <phase>Wave 1 ‚Äî Engine + Wrappers + Sub-Components</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>4</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>020</dependencies>
    <blocks>028</blocks>
    <tags>react, frontend, communication</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Draft mode mutates an existing record (Save Draft updates; Send transitions statuscode); needs careful handling of optimistic-concurrency and re-load on resume; user-data preservation matters. FULL appropriate.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>F</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <fr-refs>FR-13</fr-refs>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Implement `draft` mode behavior in `EmailComposer/modes/draftMode.ts` (pure logic) + integration in the reducer + send path.

    Load behavior (FR-13):
    - Engine receives `sourceRecord` for the draft from SendEmailPage wrapper (loaded via Xrm.WebApi.retrieveRecord('sprk_communication', communicationId) where the wrapper's load checks `statuscode === Draft`)
    - All editable fields populated from sourceRecord (similar to compose pre-fill, but the record exists)
    - The composer is now editing AN EXISTING RECORD, not creating a new one ‚Äî important for the saveDraft + send paths

    Save Draft behavior:
    - Calls a new `updateCommunicationDraft(communicationId, fields)` typed wrapper (likely needs adding to `communicationApi.ts`) ‚Äî PATCH/PUT to `sprk_communication` (via Xrm.WebApi or BFF) updating mutable fields: subject, body, bodyFormat, recipients (collection), attachments
    - Does NOT transition statuscode (still Draft)
    - Validation: only `TO_INVALID_EMAIL` blocks Save Draft (allows empty subject/body) ‚Äî per task 020 contract

    Send behavior:
    - Validates fully (all canonical codes)
    - Posts to `/api/communications/send` via `sendCommunication()` with `existingCommunicationId: communicationId` ‚Äî server-side logic: if existingCommunicationId present, update the record + transition statuscode to Sent + invoke Graph SendMail (vs the compose path which creates a new record + sends)
    - **Note**: this may require a coordination check with Wave 0 task 005 (`sendCommunication()` wrapper refinements) ‚Äî if `existingCommunicationId` is not yet in the wrapper API, add it as part of this task and coordinate the BFF DTO `SendCommunicationRequest.ExistingCommunicationId` field (per FR-22 Wave 0 spec). If the BFF doesn't yet support it, document the gap in task notes; ship the client-side intent; coordinate BFF update via PR description (may require ad-hoc Wave 0 follow-up).

    Discard behavior:
    - Delete the draft record (via Xrm.WebApi.deleteRecord) + invoke `onClose`

    Files:
    - `modes/draftMode.ts` (NEW) ‚Äî load logic + save/send flag computation
    - Update reducer to handle `mode === 'draft' &amp;&amp; sourceRecord` initialState
    - Update engine send-path to include `existingCommunicationId` when in draft mode
    - Update `communicationApi.ts` if `updateCommunicationDraft()` doesn't exist; or use Xrm.WebApi directly
  </prompt>

  <role>
    React + TypeScript developer comfortable with Dataverse upsert semantics + Xrm.WebApi + the existing-record-vs-new-record send distinction.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Draft mode loads a Draft `sprk_communication` record; Save Draft updates it (statuscode unchanged); Send transitions to Sent + invokes Graph SendMail. Discard deletes the record. `npm run build` + `npm run lint` clean.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per FR-13: drafts are first-class ‚Äî composer needs to round-trip them. The server-side path supports it: `sprk_communication` rows with `statuscode = Draft` simply aren't picked up by the send pipeline. The composer is responsible for the statuscode transition on send.

      Xrm.WebApi vs BFF for draft save: per `docs/standards/DATA-ACCESS-DECISION-CRITERIA.md`, mutating Dataverse records from a Code Page should use Xrm.WebApi (host-context preferred) unless there's a side effect (e.g., authorization, audit) that only the BFF provides. Draft updates have no side effects beyond Dataverse ‚Üí Xrm.WebApi.updateRecord is fine for Save Draft.

      Send IS a side-effect path ‚Üí must go through BFF `/api/communications/send`. The BFF needs to know "this is an existing record, transition it; don't create a new one." That's the `existingCommunicationId` field.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/modes/draftMode.ts (NEW)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/EmailComposer.reducer.ts (UPDATE)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/EmailComposer.tsx (UPDATE ‚Äî saveDraft + send for draft mode)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/services/communicationApi.ts (POSSIBLY UPDATE ‚Äî existingCommunicationId field)</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Communication/Models/SendCommunicationRequest.cs (COORDINATE ‚Äî ExistingCommunicationId field)</file>
      <file>docs/standards/DATA-ACCESS-DECISION-CRITERIA.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">Send errors as SendCommunicationError</constraint>
