  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Compose-mode-first-save: when a user clicks Save Draft from compose mode (no existing record), the path is "create + statuscode Draft". This could be added either as a creation via Xrm.WebApi.createRecord OR a new BFF endpoint. For Wave 1, simpler to use Xrm.WebApi.createRecord('sprk_communication', { ...mapStateToDraftUpdate(state), statuscode: Draft }) and set `existingCommunicationId` to the returned id. Document the choice.

    `existingCommunicationId` BFF coordination: if the BFF doesn't accept it, this task's send-from-draft path doesn't work end-to-end. The fallback is "client just doesn't transition statuscode; server treats it as a new record". The Owner may need to weigh in on whether to add the BFF field as part of Wave 0 follow-up or to defer draft-from-page send to a later wave. Document in PR.
  </notes>

